  "learn": {
    "heading": "x is across, y is up or down",
    "intro": "<p>Every point is an <strong>ordered pair (x, y)</strong>. The x is across: <em>right</em> or <em>left</em>. The y is vertical: <em>up</em> or <em>down</em>. Left and right are opposites, and up and down are opposites — that is the only new idea for all four quadrants.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>(2, 5):</strong> 2 right, 5 up.",
      "<strong>Opposites:</strong> if right is the positive direction, then left is the opposite. If up is positive, down is the opposite."
    ]
